# Framework changes require documentation updates

Any change to the Synapse **engine or how it is used** must update the matching docs in the **same change** (same commit/PR). Shipping behavior without docs is drift.

## What counts as a framework change

- Engine code: `lib/**`, `bin/**`, `agents.sh`, `package.json`, `schema/**`
- CLI surface: subcommands, flags, shell wrappers (`synapse …` / `vault-*`), install/setup
- Manifest dialect, roles/profiles, lint rules, SQL tooling (`migrate` / `index` / `views`)
- Agents, rules, loops, governance, privacy gate, or ontology types (e.g. `hub`)
- Package boundary: what ships in `@eborja/synapse` vs what stays in a consumer vault

## Docs to bring current (pick what the change touches)

| If you changed… | Update at least… |
|---|---|
| Install / consume / package layout | `README.md`, `docs/doc-fork-and-extend.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` |
| CLI commands or env vars | `docs/doc-cli-reference.md`, `README.md` quick start, `AGENTS.md` |
| Agent launch / runtime / `--cli` | `docs/doc-runtime-wiring.md`, `TUTORIAL.md`, `AGENTS.md` |
| Engine behavior (render/lint/augment) | `_meta/context-engine-guide.md`, relevant `tools/tool-*.md` |
| Types / hubs / ontology | `_meta/conventions.md`, `hub-synapse.md`, domain hub notes |
| User-facing overview | `README.md`, `TUTORIAL.md`, `AGENTS.md` (always for framework-wide changes) |

Also update the vault rule note [[rule-framework-docs-current]] when the *policy* itself changes.

## Checklist before finishing

1. Search docs for **old command names** (`node _meta/tools/…`, `vault-mocs`, `moc-`, removed flags).
2. Prefer `synapse <sub>` examples; note `vault-*` only as equals where they still exist.
3. Add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry when the change is user-visible (CLI, package API, breaking dialect).
4. Do **not** leave "TODO: update docs" — either update them or split docs into a follow-up that lands with the same PR.

## Out of scope

Pure refactors with **zero** user/agent-visible behavior change do not require README rewrites — still update code comments / `CHANGELOG` only if the public API surface moved.
